<br>
Wayne’s take on Jim’s army version 1.1 <br>
<br>
Grey Death Armies in 40K! <br>
<br>
HQ – Space Marine Heroes; Librarian*; Chaplain; (each with Grey Death Bodyguard* upgrade option, this replaces the normal command squad) <br>
<br>
Elite – Terminator Squad; Terminator Assault Squad; Dreadnought; Sandman Squad* <br>
<br>
Troops – 1+ Grey Death Tactical Squad*; 1+ Scout Squad <br>
<br>
Fast Attack – Assault Squad*; Bike Squadron; Attack Bike Squadron; Scout Bike Squadron; Land Speeder Squadron*; Scout Battle Suit Squad* <br>
<br>
Heavy Support - 0-1 Predator (Annihilator or Destructor), 0-1 Vindicator, 0-1 Whirlwind; 0-1 Land Raider; 0-1 Land Raider Crusader <br>
<br>
Everything with a (*) has special rules or options. See below for the changes. Any selection without an asterisk is exactly as described in Codex: Space Marines. <br>
<br>
HQ <br>
<br>
Grey Death Librarians are exactly the same as Normal Librarians with the exception of their Psychic Power. Grey Death Librarians have a unique ability to slightly alter the time stream. During his own Shooting Phase the Librarian may attempt to cast “Temporal Distortion” on any friendly model within 18 inches. The model, which can be any infantry, bike or walker (including Scout Battle Suits and Dreadnoughts), but not a tank, may shoot twice in the shooting phase. This will however prevent the model (and the unit it is with) from assaulting in the assault phase.  <br>
