<br>
Special Rules: <br>
<br>
Agile: Scout Battle Suits can move 9 inches in the movement phase and 9 inches when assaulting. They re-roll difficult terrain checks yet still only sweeping advance and fall back 2D6”. <br>
<br>
Scouts: Scout Battle Suits are often used to scout ahead of the main force. This allows them to be placed on the board even in scenarios where they would not normally be deployed. If you are playing a mission where a limited number of troops can be deployed, Scout Battle Suits do not count towards this maximum. In addition to this they may always choose to make a free move after both sides have deployed but before either side has moved. <br>
<br>
Scout Battle Suits in Difficult Terrain: Scout Battle Suits are affected by Terrain like bikes. Any model entering difficult terrain must roll a D6, on the roll of a 1 the suit is destroyed. Scout Battle Suits are excellent at using cover, however, and are allowed to re-roll difficult terrain checks. <br>
<br>
Mobile, Agile and Hostile: Scout Battle Suits always count as being stationary for the purposes of firing rapid-fire weaponry. This means Scout Battle Suits will be able to shoot at one target and assault another, and will still receive the +1 attack for charging under the new assault rules.<br>
